3. **Amplifier (Differential or Gain Stage)**: Scales the voltage from the potentiometer to match the input range of the DAQ while maintaining the center position (90 degrees) to 0 V. It also shifts the signal so that the entire range of the potentiometer corresponds to the -7V to +7V input range of the DAQ.

4. **Filter_50Hz**: A notch filter designed to attenuate the noise at 50 Hz. This is necessary to ensure that the power line interference common in many regions does not affect the accuracy of the signal.

5. **Filter_60Hz**: A similar notch filter but designed to attenuate 60 Hz noise, which is the common power line frequency in other regions.

6. **Anti-Aliasing Filter**: A low-pass filter that removes high-frequency noise and signals above the Nyquist frequency (half the DAQ sampling rate, i.e., 500 Hz) to prevent aliasing when the analog signal is digitized by the DAQ.

7. **DAQ (Data Acquisition System)**: Samples the conditioned analog signal at a rate of 1000 samples per second and converts it to digital data for further processing or display. It is important to ensure that the signal is within the acceptable input voltage range and adequately filtered before reaching this stage.
```

